com.opengamma.strata.calc.marketdata.function

Interface TimeSeriesProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MissingDataAwareTimeSeriesProvider

    public interface TimeSeriesProvider
    A source of time series of observable market data.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static TimeSeriesProvider empty()
      Returns a time-series provider that returns an empty time series for any ID.
      static TimeSeriesProvider none()
      Returns a time-series provider that is unable to source any time-series.

    • Method Detail

      • none

        static TimeSeriesProvider none()
        Returns a time-series provider that is unable to source any time-series.

        This is useful when it is not necessary for the engine to source time-series on-demand, for example because all market data is being provided in a snapshot.

        Returns:
        the time-series provider

      • empty

        static TimeSeriesProvider empty()
        Returns a time-series provider that returns an empty time series for any ID.

        This is useful when calculations might require a time series and therefore request it but the user knows that in the current case the time series data won't be used.

        Returns:
        the time-series provider

      • timeSeries

        Result<LocalDateDoubleTimeSeries> timeSeries(ObservableId id)
        Returns a time series of market data for the specified ID.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the market data in the time series
        Returns:
        a time series of market data for the specified ID
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if there is no time series available for the specified ID
